<subSubSection id="C354656399501131FF37FB70FE58FAB3" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF136E899501131FF37FB70FE58FAB3" blockId="81.[123,652,193,1389]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet is a Latin adjective that means ‘‘with a mole or birthmark’’. I refer to the flecklike appearance of the elytral middescal setal tuft.</paragraph>
